description: Binary orders (A029837) of consecutive primorial numbers (A002110).
comments: These orders determines the maximal numbers of unitary divisors valid for integers in given binary order ranges (see A046971).
example: The sixth primorial number is Q_6=2*3*5*7*11*13=30030 which is in the range of [ 16384,32766 ]=[ 2^14,2^15 ], so its binary order is a[ 6 ]=15
author: _Labos Elemer_
